{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T11:48:03.030Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Denoising Autoencoders — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Denoising Autoencoders Are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Denoising Autoencoders (DAEs)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are a stochastic version of standard autoencoders that are trained to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "reconstruct the original clean input from a corrupted (noisy) version"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Unlike traditional autoencoders that learn to copy input to output, DAEs force the network to learn meaningful features by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "adding intentional noise to input data and then reconstructing the clean original"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of a denoising autoencoder as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "digital janitor"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that cleans a messy blackboard covered in scribbles (noise) to reveal the meaningful text (data) hidden underneath."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Denoising Autoencoders Matter in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "DAEs are crucial for generative AI because they:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Capability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Application"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Remove noise from data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Medical imaging, speech enhancement, satellite data analysis"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learn robust representations"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature extraction for classification, clustering"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevent overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Regularization technique that prevents models from copying inputs to outputs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Improve generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model becomes robust to noise in real-world data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data pre-processing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Clean noisy inputs before feeding to other models"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Denoising Autoencoders Work (Core Process)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The 4-step training process:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: CORRUPTION (Add Noise)\n  Original clean input: x\n  Add noise (Gaussian, masking, salt-and-pepper)\n  Corrupted input: x̃ (x with noise)\n\nStep 2: ENCODING (Compress)\n  x̃ → Encoder → Latent code: h = f(x̃)\n  Encoder learns to capture essential features robust to noise\n\nStep 3: DECODING (Reconstruct)\n  h → Decoder → Reconstructed output: x̂ = g(h)\n  Decoder attempts to reconstruct clean original x\n\nStep 4: LOSS (Compare with Clean, Not Noisy)\n  Compare x̂ (reconstructed) with x (original clean)\n  NOT with x̃ (noisy input)\n  Loss = ||x - x̂||² (e.g., MSE)\n  \nRepeat: Update weights to minimize loss"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key difference"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The reconstruction is compared to the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "original clean data (not the corrupted version)"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Training Process in Detail"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step-by-step with example:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "sql"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: Get training sample\n  Input image: Clear photo of a cat\n  \nStep 2: Add noise stochastically\n  Technique: Masking noise (set 30-50% random pixels to 0)\n  Corrupted: Blurry photo with black spots ← NOISY\n  \nStep 3: Encode corrupted input\n  Encoder compresses blurry photo to 32-unit latent vector\n  \nStep 4: Decode latent vector\n  Decoder reconstructs 32 units back to full image\n  \nStep 5: Compare with ORIGINAL (NOT corrupted)\n  Reconstructed: Clear photo of cat (supposedly)\n  Original: Clear photo of cat (from training data)\n  Loss: Compare reconstructed vs. original\n  \nStep 6: Backpropagate loss\n  Update encoder/decoder weights to minimize loss"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why this works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The autoencoder can't simply copy the input to output because the input contains random noise."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Types of Noise Used for Corruption"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Noise Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gaussian Noise"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add random values from Gaussian distribution"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Continuous data (images, audio)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Masking Noise"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Randomly set 30-50% of input nodes to zero"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Images, text"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Salt-and-Pepper Noise"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Random pixels set to maximum/minimum value"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Binary images"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Recommended corruption"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Set "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "30-50% of random input nodes to zero"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for masking noise."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Difference: DAE vs. Standard Autoencoder"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard Autoencoder"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Denoising Autoencoder"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Input"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Clean original "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Corrupted noisy "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\tilde{x}"}}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Target"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reconstruct "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reconstruct clean "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " from noisy "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\tilde{x}"}}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "L(x, g(f(x)))"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "L(x, g(f(\\tilde{x})))"}}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can learn identity function (copy)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Must undo corruption, can't copy"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "May just copy input"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learns to ignore noise, focus on features"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "The solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": DAEs "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "corrupt the data input"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to prevent learning the identity function."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Stochastic Nature of DAEs"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "DAEs are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "stochastic"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (random/probabilistic):"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Corruption process"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conditional distribution \\( C(\\tilde{x}"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "x) \\) over corrupted samples given data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Randomness"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different noise added each time (random 30-50% of inputs to zero)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training pairs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learns from "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "(x, \\tilde{x})"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " pairs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reconstruction distribution"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Estimates \\( p"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{reconstruct}}(x"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\\tilde{x}) \\)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "At every single pass, different variables will be corrupted randomly."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits of Denoising Autoencoders"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Robustness to noise"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Network becomes robust to noise in input data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature extraction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learns meaningful representations for downstream tasks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevents overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Regularization technique that prevents identity function learning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Better generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Improved ability to generalize by training on noisy data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Captures significant features"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learns to prioritize most important features"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs & Limitations"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Noise level critical"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Too little noise = almost standard AE; too much = unrecoverable"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training complexity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Requires corruption process + clean targets"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computational cost"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slightly more expensive due to corruption step"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data dependent"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Need clean training data to compare against"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How much noise to add"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": This is a critical trade-off."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example: Image Denoising Application"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scenario: Clean up noisy medical X-ray images\n\nStep 1: Training data\n  10,000 clean X-ray images (healthcare database)\n\nStep 2: Add noise to inputs\n  Gaussian noise: Add random values to pixel intensities\n  Corrupted: 10,000 noisy X-ray images\n  \nStep 3: Train DAE\n  Input: Noisy X-ray\n  Encoder: Compress to 64 units\n  Decoder: Reconstruct to 1024×1024 pixels\n  Target: Clean X-ray (from original database)\n  Loss: Compare reconstructed vs. clean\n  \nStep 4: Use trained model\n  Input: New noisy X-ray from patient\n  Output: Clean X-ray (noise removed)\n  Result: Medical professional can diagnose accurately"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The model learns to capture essential features (bone structure, organs) while ignoring noise."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of denoising autoencoders as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "learning to read through fog"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Standard autoencoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": You see a clear sign \"HELLO\" and copy it to \"HELLO\" (just copying)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Denoising autoencoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": You see a blurry sign \"H "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "strike"}], "text": "LL@\" through fog and must reconstruct \"HELLO\" (learning to see through noise)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": You learn to recognize the actual letters, not just copy what you see"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Or think of it as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "restoration expert"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Input"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": A damaged painting with scratches and dirt"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Process"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The expert studies the damaged version"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The restored, original painting (without scratches)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Compare the restored version with photos of the original painting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Denoising Autoencoders (DAEs)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " reconstruct the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "original clean input "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " from a corrupted (noisy) version "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\tilde{x}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "**"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Corruption process"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Add noise (Gaussian, masking 30-50% zeros, salt-and-pepper) to input before encoding"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss compares reconstructed output with clean original"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (not the noisy input)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevents identity function"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cannot simply copy input because input contains random noise"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stochastic"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Different noise added each training pass (random corruption)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learns robust features"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Network learns to ignore noise and focus on significant data distribution features"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Applications"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Medical imaging, speech enhancement, data cleaning, feature extraction, anomaly detection"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regularization technique"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Prevents overfitting by forcing meaningful feature learning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Denoising Autoencoders enable models to learn robust representations by removing noise and capturing the underlying data distribution, making them essential for data pre-processing and feature extraction in generative AI."}]}]}}